#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:146
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:154
msgid "Welcome to Wesnoth!"
msgstr "Welcome to Wesnoth!"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:148
msgid ""
"For this tutorial, you are playing Konrad. You are standing on the keep, and "
"your mentor Delfador is on the east side of the river. You can move the "
"mouse over a unit to see a summary of its abilities and stats on the right "
"of the screen."
msgstr ""
"For this tutorial, you are playing Konrad. You are standing on the keep, and "
"your mentor Delfador is on the east side of the river. You can move the "
"mouse over a unit to see a summary of its abilities and stats on the right "
"of the screen."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:156
msgid ""
"For this tutorial, you are playing Li’sar. You are standing on the keep, and "
"your mentor Delfador is on the east side of the river. you can move the "
"mouse over a unit to see a summary of its abilities and stats on the right "
"of the screen."
msgstr ""
"For this tutorial, you are playing Li’sar. You are standing on the keep, and "
"your mentor Delfador is on the east side of the river. you can move the "
"mouse over a unit to see a summary of its abilities and stats on the right "
"of the screen."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:162
msgid "Click on Konrad"
msgstr "Click on Konrad"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:164
msgid "Click on Li’sar"
msgstr "Click on Li’sar"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:198
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:206
msgid "Movement"
msgstr "Movement"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:200
msgid ""
"When you select a unit, in this case Konrad, the places he can move to are "
"highlighted. All units have a certain number of <i>movement points</i>, "
"which dictate how many hexes that unit can move per turn. Normally, moving "
"one hex uses one movement point, but moving across different types of hexes, "
"or <i>terrains</i>, can use up more. You will learn more about that later. "
"To move, simply click on your destination. You can press <b>u</b> to undo a "
"move if you move to the wrong place."
msgstr ""
"When you select a unit, in this case Konrad, the places he can move to are "
"highlighted. All units have a certain number of <i>movement points</i>, "
"which dictate how many hexes that unit can move per turn. Normally, moving "
"one hex uses one movement point, but moving across different types of hexes, "
"or <i>terrains</i>, can use up more. You will learn more about that later. "
"To move, simply click on your destination. You can press <b>u</b> to undo a "
"move if you move to the wrong place."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:208
msgid ""
"When you select a unit, in this case Li’sar, the places she can move to are "
"highlighted. All units have a certain number of <i>movement points</i>, "
"which dictate how many hexes that unit can move per turn. Normally, moving "
"one hex uses one movement point, but moving across different types of hexes, "
"or <i>terrains</i>, can use up more. You will learn more about that later. "
"To move, simply click on your destination. You can press <b>u</b> to undo a "
"move if you move to the wrong place."
msgstr ""
"When you select a unit, in this case Li’sar, the places she can move to are "
"highlighted. All units have a certain number of <i>movement points</i>, "
"which dictate how many hexes that unit can move per turn. Normally, moving "
"one hex uses one movement point, but moving across different types of hexes, "
"or <i>terrains</i>, can use up more. You will learn more about that later. "
"To move, simply click on your destination. You can press <b>u</b> to undo a "
"move if you move to the wrong place."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:214
msgid "Move Konrad next to Delfador."
msgstr "Move Konrad next to Delfador."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:216
msgid "Move Li’sar next to Delfador."
msgstr "Move Li’sar next to Delfador."

#. [message]: speaker=student
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:233
msgid "Good morning, Delfador! Is it time to attack things?"
msgstr "Good morning, Delfador! Is it time to attack things?"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:238
msgid "Um, well..."
msgstr "Um, well..."

#. [message]: speaker=student
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:243
msgid "Have you found an orc for me to fight, huh? A troll?"
msgstr "Have you found an orc for me to fight, huh? A troll?"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:248
msgid "Quiet! I will summon an enemy for you..."
msgstr "Quiet! I will summon an enemy for you..."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:295
msgid "... this quintain!"
msgstr "... this quintain!"

#. [message]: speaker=student
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:300
msgid "A quintain? You want me to fight a dummy?"
msgstr "A quintain? You want me to fight a dummy?"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:306
msgid ""
"You have $student_hp hitpoints and a sword, boy. I’m fairly sure you’ll win."
msgstr ""
"You have $student_hp hit-points and a sword, boy. I’m fairly sure you’ll win."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:311
msgid ""
"female^Young lady, you have $student_hp hitpoints and a sword. I’m fairly "
"sure you’ll win."
msgstr ""
"Young lady, you have $student_hp hit-points and a sword. I’m fairly sure "
"you’ll win."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:319
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:326
msgid "Attacking"
msgstr "Attacking"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:321
msgid ""
"To attack the quintain, first select the attacker (Konrad) then the target "
"(the quintain). You will see an attack description. When you click <b>OK</"
"b>, Konrad will attack."
msgstr ""
"To attack the quintain, first select the attacker (Konrad) then the target "
"(the quintain). You will see an attack description. When you click <b>OK</"
"b>, Konrad will attack."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:328
msgid ""
"To attack the quintain, first select the attacker (Li’sar) then the target "
"(the quintain). You will see an attack description. When you click <b>OK</"
"b>, Li’sar will attack."
msgstr ""
"To attack the quintain, first select the attacker (Li’sar) then the target "
"(the quintain). You will see an attack description. When you click <b>OK</"
"b>, Li’sar will attack."

#. [message]: speaker=student
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:343
msgid "Hey! This quintain fights back!"
msgstr "Hey! This quintain fights back!"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:348
msgid "Hmm, perhaps we should have started with a doll."
msgstr "Hmm, perhaps we should have started with a doll."

#. [message]: speaker=student
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:353
msgid "Should I retreat?"
msgstr "Should I retreat?"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#. [message]: speaker=Galdrad
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:358
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:659
msgid "Good idea!"
msgstr "Good idea!"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:364
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:371
msgid "Crowns"
msgstr "Crowns"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:366
msgid ""
"The tiny golden crown above your leader (Konrad) indicates he is a side "
"leader. In most scenarios, you will lose if your leader is killed. Be sure "
"to keep him safe!"
msgstr ""
"The tiny golden crown above your leader (Konrad) indicates he is a side "
"leader. In most scenarios, you will lose if your leader is killed. Be sure "
"to keep him safe!"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:373
msgid ""
"The tiny golden crown above your leader (Li’sar) indicates she is a side "
"leader. In most scenarios, you will lose if your leader is killed. Be sure "
"to keep her safe!"
msgstr ""
"The tiny golden crown above your leader (Li’sar) indicates she is a side "
"leader. In most scenarios, you will lose if your leader is killed. Be sure "
"to keep her safe!"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:383
msgid ""
"Unfortunately, you’ve used up your turn attacking the quintain. The quintain "
"now gets to attack."
msgstr ""
"Unfortunately, you’ve used up your turn attacking the quintain. The quintain "
"now gets to attack."

#. [message]: speaker=student
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:388
msgid "The <i>dummy</i> gets a turn?"
msgstr "The <i>dummy</i> gets a turn?"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:393
msgid ""
"Yes. It’s a magical quintain! It gets 5 chances to hit you for 3 damage "
"each. If it hits every time, you’ll drop from $student_hp to "
"$($student_hp-15) hitpoints. Brace yourself!"
msgstr ""
"Yes. It’s a magical quintain! It gets 5 chances to hit you for 3 damage "
"each. If it hits every time, you’ll drop from $student_hp to "
"$($student_hp-15) hit-points. Brace yourself!"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:400
msgid "Turns"
msgstr "Turns"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:402
msgid ""
"Every turn, each side in a scenario gets a chance to make their move. Once "
"you’ve completed everything you wish to do this turn, click on the <b>End "
"Turn</b> button in the bottom right of the screen. The other teams, whether "
"controlled by the AI or other human players, will then make their move. Some "
"scenarios must be completed in a certain number of turns. You can see what "
"turn it is, and any applicable turn limit, next to the flag icon at the top "
"of the screen."
msgstr ""
"Every turn, each side in a scenario gets a chance to make their move. Once "
"you’ve completed everything you wish to do this turn, click on the <b>End "
"Turn</b> button in the bottom right of the screen. The other teams, whether "
"controlled by the AI or other human players, will then make their move. Some "
"scenarios must be completed in a certain number of turns. You can see what "
"turn it is, and any applicable turn limit, next to the flag icon at the top "
"of the screen."

#. [event]
#. [event]: (id=Delfador) 14 8}, (id=Delfador) facing nw}
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:405
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:451
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:536
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:334
msgid "End your turn"
msgstr "End your turn"

#. [message]: speaker=student
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:420
msgid "Ouch! I need to heal! Only $student_hp hitpoints left!"
msgstr "Ouch! I need to heal! Only $student_hp hit-points left!"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:425
msgid ""
"There are two villages within your reach. Visiting villages is a good idea, "
"and ending your turn on one will heal you. To a village!"
msgstr ""
"There are two villages within your reach. Visiting villages is a good idea, "
"and ending your turn on one will heal you. To a village!"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:429
msgid "Move Konrad to a nearby village"
msgstr "Move Konrad to a nearby village"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:431
msgid "Move Li’sar to a nearby village"
msgstr "Move Li’sar to a nearby village"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:444
msgid "Villages"
msgstr "Villages"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:446
msgid ""
"You have captured a village! It now flies your colors and has been added to "
"your total village count (the house icon at the top of the screen shows how "
"many villages you currently control). Villages provide the gold needed to "
"recruit units. Each turn, you gain two gold plus one for every village you "
"own."
msgstr ""
"You have captured a village! It now flies your colours and has been added to "
"your total village count (the house icon at the top of the screen shows how "
"many villages you currently control). Villages provide the gold needed to "
"recruit units. Each turn, you gain two gold plus one for every village you "
"own."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:466
msgid ""
"Since you started your turn on a village, you regained some health! Villages "
"heal units 8 hitpoints per turn, or enough to top off their health, "
"whichever is less. In your case, you regained $student_hp_heal_amount "
"hitpoints."
msgstr ""
"Since you started your turn on a village, you regained some health! Villages "
"heal units 8 hit-points per turn, or enough to top off their health, "
"whichever is less. In your case, you regained $student_hp_heal_amount hit-"
"points."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:471
msgid "Now, it’s time to summon some help against that quintain."
msgstr "Now, it’s time to summon some help against that quintain."

#. [message]: speaker=student
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:476
msgid "I’ll recruit some elves!"
msgstr "I’ll recruit some elves!"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:481
msgid ""
"A splendid idea! It’s probably best not to attempt attacking the quintain "
"this turn. Instead, you should return to the keep and recruit two units; you "
"have plenty of gold for that."
msgstr ""
"A splendid idea! It’s probably best not to attempt attacking the quintain "
"this turn. Instead, you should return to the keep and recruit two units; you "
"have plenty of gold for that."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:485
msgid "Move Konrad to the keep"
msgstr "Move Konrad to the keep"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:487
msgid "Move Li’sar to the keep"
msgstr "Move Li’sar to the keep"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:505
msgid "Recruiting"
msgstr "Recruiting"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:507
msgid ""
"Whenever you’re on a <i>keep</i>, you can <i>recruit</i> units on the castle "
"tiles around it by right-clicking and selecting <b>Recruit</b>. Note that "
"newly recruited units cannot act the turn you recruit them; you will be able "
"to use them next turn. This scenario you have only one type of unit to "
"choose from: the Elvish Fighter."
msgstr ""
"Whenever you’re on a <i>keep</i>, you can <i>recruit</i> units on the castle "
"tiles around it by right-clicking and selecting <b>Recruit</b>. Note that "
"newly recruited units cannot act the turn you recruit them; you will be able "
"to use them next turn. This scenario you have only one type of unit to "
"choose from: the Elvish Fighter."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:510
msgid "Recruit two Elvish Fighters"
msgstr "Recruit two Elvish Fighters"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:529
msgid "Traits"
msgstr "Traits"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:531
msgid ""
"Be sure to examine the <i>traits</i> of your new recruits. They are listed "
"under its race in the sidebar. Traits can subtly affect how you use your "
"troops. For example, units with the <i>quick</i> trait can move a extra hex "
"each turn, or units with the <i>intelligent</i> trait require 20% less "
"experience to level up. A full list of all possible traits may be found in "
"help."
msgstr ""
"Be sure to examine the <i>traits</i> of your new recruits. They are listed "
"under its race in the sidebar. Traits can subtly affect how you use your "
"troops. For example, units with the <i>quick</i> trait can move a extra hex "
"each turn, or units with the <i>intelligent</i> trait require 20% less "
"experience to level up. A full list of all possible traits may be found in "
"help."

#. [message]: speaker=student
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:565
msgid ""
"Hey, the quintain just healed 2 hitpoints! I’d better attack it at once!"
msgstr ""
"Hey, the quintain just healed 2 hit-points! I’d better attack it at once!"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:570
msgid "Yes, if a unit doesn’t do anything for a turn, it will slowly heal."
msgstr "Yes, if a unit doesn’t do anything for a turn, it will slowly heal."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:575
msgid ""
"Before you send your fighters against the quintain, you should know they "
"have two kinds of attack..."
msgstr ""
"Before you send your fighters against the quintain, you should know they "
"have two kinds of attack..."

#. [message]: speaker=student
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:580
msgid "I’ll tell them to use the one that does the most damage!"
msgstr "I’ll tell them to use the one that does the most damage!"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:585
msgid ""
"And which would that be? The sword (5–4) or the bow (3–3)? I suppose you’ll "
"find out..."
msgstr ""
"And which would that be? The sword (5–4) or the bow (3–3)? I suppose you’ll "
"find out..."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:588
msgid "Attack the quintain with your fighters"
msgstr "Attack the quintain with your fighters"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:606
msgid ""
"You wouldn’t do anything stupid like charging that quintain yourself again, "
"now would you? Use the fighters you recruited first; they’ll be a lot of "
"help."
msgstr ""
"You wouldn’t do anything stupid like charging that quintain yourself again, "
"now would you? Use the fighters you recruited first; they’ll be a lot of "
"help."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:635
msgid ""
"Your elf used a sword (5–4; or 5 damage, 4 attacks), which is a <i>melee</i> "
"attack. The quintain defended with its melee attack (3–5). The ranged attack "
"(the bow) would have been safer."
msgstr ""
"Your elf used a sword (5–4; or 5 damage, 4 attacks), which is a <i>melee</i> "
"attack. The quintain defended with its melee attack (3–5). The ranged attack "
"(the bow) would have been safer."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:647
msgid ""
"Your elf used a bow, which is a <i>ranged</i> attack (3–3; or 3 damage, 3 "
"attacks). The quintain has no ranged attack, only a melee attack, so it "
"could not defend itself."
msgstr ""
"Your elf used a bow, which is a <i>ranged</i> attack (3–3; or 3 damage, 3 "
"attacks). The quintain has no ranged attack, only a melee attack, so it "
"could not defend itself."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:662
msgid "Keep attacking with both elves until the quintain is finished!"
msgstr "Keep attacking with both elves until the quintain is finished!"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:677
msgid "Maybe you should recruit another elf?"
msgstr "Maybe you should recruit another elf?"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:687
msgid "Unit Descriptions"
msgstr "Unit Descriptions"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:689
msgid ""
"You can right click on a unit to see a detailed <b>Unit Description</b>."
msgstr ""
"You can right-click on a unit to see a detailed <b>Unit Description</b>."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:699
msgid "Protect Your Troops"
msgstr "Protect Your Troops"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:701
msgid ""
"Remember to pull back wounded units into villages and recruit more if "
"needed. Take special care of units with the highest <i>experience points "
"(XP)</i> so they can gain levels and become more powerful."
msgstr ""
"Remember to pull back wounded units into villages and recruit more if "
"needed. Take special care of units with the highest <i>experience points "
"(XP)</i> so they can gain levels and become more powerful."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:711
msgid "Support"
msgstr "Support"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:713
msgid ""
"Each village you control will <i>support</i> one unit for free. After that, "
"each unit costs you one gold per turn."
msgstr ""
"Each village you control will <i>support</i> one unit for free. After that, "
"each unit costs you one gold per turn."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:723
msgid "You had really better finish off that quintain."
msgstr "You had really better finish off that quintain."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:733
msgid "Advancement"
msgstr "Advancement"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:735
msgid ""
"When a unit gains enough experience points (the <i>experience bar</i>, if "
"present, is on the <b>right</b> of the <i>hitpoints bar</i>), it will gain a "
"level. Elvish Fighters have two advancement options, and you will be able to "
"choose which one you want. However, second level units cost twice as much to "
"support as first level units."
msgstr ""
"When a unit gains enough experience points (the <i>experience bar</i>, if "
"present, is on the <b>right</b> of the <i>hit-points bar</i>), it will gain "
"a level. Elvish Fighters have two advancement options, and you will be able "
"to choose which one you want. However, second level units cost twice as much "
"to support as first level units."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:745
msgid "Defenses"
msgstr "Defences"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:748
msgid ""
"Whenever one of your units is selected, you’ll see varying percentages as "
"you move the mouse over the map. The higher the percentage, the more "
"<i>defense</i> that unit has in that kind of terrain. For example, most "
"units have good defenses in castles and villages but poor defenses in "
"rivers. However, these quintains use a <i>magical</i> attack, which always "
"has a 70% chance of hitting no matter what terrain its target occupies."
msgstr ""
"Whenever one of your units is selected, you’ll see varying percentages as "
"you move the mouse over the map. The higher the percentage, the more "
"<i>defence</i> that unit has in that kind of terrain. For example, most "
"units have good defences in castles and villages but poor defences in "
"rivers. However, these quintains use a <i>magical</i> attack, which always "
"has a 70% chance of hitting no matter what terrain its target occupies."

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:760
msgid "Agh! This training is too much for me..."
msgstr "Agh! This training is too much for me..."

#. [message]: speaker=second_unit
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:790
msgid "The quintain is destroyed, and I have gained more experience!"
msgstr "The quintain is destroyed, and I have gained more experience!"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:795
msgid ""
"Yes, you gain experience through battle, especially by killing an opponent. "
"Gain enough experience and you’ll become more powerful."
msgstr ""
"Yes, you gain experience through battle, especially by killing an opponent. "
"Gain enough experience and you’ll become more powerful."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:801
msgid ""
"Now, Konrad, I will leave you with more dummies to practice on! After that, "
"we have real work to do..."
msgstr ""
"Now, Konrad, I will leave you with more dummies to practise on! After that, "
"we have real work to do..."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:806
msgid ""
"Now, Li’sar, I will leave you with more dummies to practice on! After that, "
"we have real work to do..."
msgstr ""
"Now, Li’sar, I will leave you with more dummies to practise on! After that, "
"we have real work to do..."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:880
msgid "Note"
msgstr "Note"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:882
msgid ""
"These dummies only attack if you are a single tile away. With care, you "
"should be able to kill them one at a time."
msgstr ""
"These dummies only attack if you are a single tile away. With care, you "
"should be able to kill them one at a time."

# TODO: maybe move this out of this textdomain
#. [set_menu_item]: id=skip_item
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:890
msgid "End Scenario"
msgstr "End Scenario"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:905
msgid ""
"Do you want to keep practicing? You can end this scenario at any time by "
"using the <b>End Scenario</b> item in the context menu to move on to the "
"next phase of your training."
msgstr ""
"Do you want to keep practising? You can end this scenario at any time by "
"using the <b>End Scenario</b> item in the context menu to move on to the "
"next phase of your training."

#. [option]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:907
msgid "Yes, I’m still figuring it out."
msgstr "Yes, I’m still working it out."

#. [option]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:910
msgid "No, I think I’ve got it."
msgstr "No, I think I’ve got it."

#. [message]: speaker=student
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:929
msgid ""
"Well, I think I know the basics. Onwards! Maybe I can fight in a real battle "
"next?"
msgstr ""
"Well, I think I know the basics. Onwards! Maybe I can fight in a real battle "
"next?"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:945
msgid "Victory"
msgstr "Victory"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/01_Tutorial_part_1.cfg:947
msgid ""
"After your victory notice, the map will be grayed out to indicate that the "
"scenario is over; this is called <i>linger mode</i>. You will still be able "
"to examine the final positions and state of your troops and any surviving "
"enemies. When you’re finished, click the <b>End Scenario</b> button to go on "
"to the next scenario in the campaign."
msgstr ""
"After your victory notice, the map will be greyed out to indicate that the "
"scenario is over; this is called <i>linger mode</i>. You will still be able "
"to examine the final positions and state of your troops and any surviving "
"enemies. When you’re finished, click the <b>End Scenario</b> button to go on "
"to the next scenario in the campaign."

#. [tutorial]: id=2_Tutorial
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:5
msgid "Wesnoth Tutorial — Part II"
msgstr "Wesnoth Tutorial — Part II"

#. [side]: type=Orcish Warrior, id=Thrag
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:43
msgid "team_name^Orcs"
msgstr "Orcs"

#. [side]: type=Orcish Warrior, id=Thrag
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:47
msgid "Thrag"
msgstr "Thrag"

#. [unit]: id=Galdrad, type=Elvish Captain
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:79
msgid "Galdrad"
msgstr "Galdrad"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:92
msgid "I hope I have a chance to retreat after this!"
msgstr "I hope I have a chance to retreat after this!"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:93
msgid "One lucky attack by an Orcish Grunt, and I’m done for!"
msgstr "One lucky attack by an Orcish Grunt, and I’m done for!"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:94
msgid "Ouch! I could make use of some healing in a village."
msgstr "Ouch! I could make use of some healing in a village."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:95
msgid "I had better retreat, before I get caught out with such low health!"
msgstr "I had better retreat, before I get caught out with such low health!"

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:100
msgid "Defeat the Orc Leader"
msgstr "Defeat the Orc Leader"

#. [objective]: condition=lose
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:105
msgid "Death of Konrad"
msgstr "Death of Konrad"

#. [objective]: condition=lose
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:116
msgid "Death of Li’sar"
msgstr "Death of Li’sar"

#. [objective]: condition=lose
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:127
msgid "Death of Galdrad"
msgstr "Death of Galdrad"

#. [message]: speaker=student
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:142
msgid ""
"Ho, Galdrad! Has Delfador conjured something else to beat me with? A flock "
"of scarecrows, perhaps?"
msgstr ""
"Ho, Galdrad! Has Delfador conjured something else to beat me with? A flock "
"of scarecrows, perhaps?"

#. [message]: speaker=Galdrad
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:148
msgid ""
"This is no game, Konrad! Orcs have encamped across the river. This is elven "
"country; they are fools to enter here. We Elves are fast and hard to hit in "
"forests. You must defeat their leader so they never threaten us again. I "
"will advise you."
msgstr ""
"This is no game, Konrad! Orcs have encamped across the river. This is elven "
"country; they are fools to enter here. We Elves are fast and hard to hit in "
"forests. You must defeat their leader so they never threaten us again. I "
"will advise you."

#. [message]: speaker=Galdrad
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:153
msgid ""
"This is no game, Li’sar! Orcs have encamped across the river. This is elven "
"country; they are fools to enter here. We Elves are fast and hard to hit in "
"forests. You must defeat their leader so they never threaten us again. I "
"will advise you."
msgstr ""
"This is no game, Li’sar! Orcs have encamped across the river. This is elven "
"country; they are fools to enter here. We Elves are fast and hard to hit in "
"forests. You must defeat their leader so they never threaten us again. I "
"will advise you."

#. [message]: speaker=student
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:159
msgid "What should I do?"
msgstr "What should I do?"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:162
msgid ""
"First, we will have to deal with the Orcish Grunt stationed in the middle of "
"the river. He should be little trouble."
msgstr ""
"First, we will have to deal with the Orcish Grunt stationed in the middle of "
"the river. He should be little trouble."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:164
msgid ""
"By then, their leader will have recruited more units to send against us and "
"the real fight will begin."
msgstr ""
"By then, their leader will have recruited more units to send against us and "
"the real fight will begin."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:166
msgid ""
"See this dark blue water? It’s too deep for either side to cross. The orcs "
"could slowly wade through that narrow band of shallow lighter-blue water in "
"the east; but we could stand on the shore and force them to fight us from "
"the water, where they are exposed and we are protected by the forest."
msgstr ""
"See this dark blue water? It’s too deep for either side to cross. The orcs "
"could slowly wade through that narrow band of shallow lighter-blue water in "
"the east; but we could stand on the shore and force them to fight us from "
"the water, where they are exposed and we are protected by the forest."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:168
msgid ""
"The more likely attack, then, is across the bridge. That middle island is "
"the key: it has a village for healing injured units and forests in which we "
"fight so well."
msgstr ""
"The more likely attack, then, is across the bridge. That middle island is "
"the key: it has a village for healing injured units, and forest in which we "
"fight so well."

#. [message]: speaker=student
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:172
msgid "Let’s go! Attack!"
msgstr "Let’s go! Attack!"

#. [message]: speaker=Galdrad
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:177
msgid ""
"Hang on! You need to gather your forces. Or do you intend to fight the orcs "
"singlehandedly?"
msgstr ""
"Hang on! You need to gather your forces. Or do you intend to fight the orcs "
"single-handedly?"

#. [message]: speaker=Galdrad
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:190
msgid ""
"I see you have veteran troops from your training! You should <i>recall</i> "
"them as as to start off the battle with more experienced units. Think "
"carefully, though; if a unit has too little experience, it might be cheaper "
"to recruit a new one."
msgstr ""
"I see you have veteran troops from your training! You should <i>recall</i> "
"them as as to start off the battle with more experienced units. Think "
"carefully, though; if a unit has too little experience, it might be cheaper "
"to recruit a new one."

#. [message]: speaker=Galdrad
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:196
msgid ""
"Some of your units have also managed to level up. They’re even more "
"formidable, so you should recall them first."
msgstr ""
"Some of your units have also managed to level up. They’re even more "
"formidable, so you should recall them first."

#. [message]: speaker=Galdrad
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:211
msgid ""
"Unfortunately, none of your troops survived your training, so you will have "
"to recruit new units. If you had any veteran troops, you could have "
"<i>recalled</i> them to battle this scenario. More experienced units would "
"have been of help against these orcs."
msgstr ""
"Unfortunately, none of your troops survived your training, so you will have "
"to recruit new units. If you had any veteran troops, you could have "
"<i>recalled</i> them to battle this scenario. More experienced units would "
"have been of help against these orcs."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:218
msgid "Recalling"
msgstr "Recalling"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:220
msgid ""
"In addition to recruiting new units each scenario, you can also <i>recall</"
"i> your experienced veterans from previous scenarios, for the cost of 20 "
"gold each. This allows you to build up a formidable army over the course of "
"multiple scenarios by recalling your highest leveled troops or those with "
"good combinations of traits and abilities. To recall a unit, right click "
"while your leader stands on a keep and select the <i>Recall</i> option. "
"Remember to also recruit new troops in addition to recalling old ones."
msgstr ""
"In addition to recruiting new units each scenario, you can also <i>recall</"
"i> your experienced veterans from previous scenarios, for the cost of 20 "
"gold each. This allows you to build a formidable army over the course of "
"multiple scenarios by recalling your highest level troops or those with good "
"combinations of traits and abilities. To recall a unit, right-click while "
"your leader stands on a keep and select the <i>Recall</i> option. Remember "
"to also recruit new troops in addition to recalling old ones."

#. [message]: speaker=Galdrad
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:225
msgid ""
"You also have two new types of units to recruit this scenario: Elvish "
"Archers and Elvish Shamans. I’ll tell you more about them when you recruit "
"them. Personally, I would recommend a balanced force of two archers, two "
"fighters, and a shaman."
msgstr ""
"You also have two new types of units to recruit this scenario: Elvish "
"Archers and Elvish Shamans. I’ll tell you more about them when you recruit "
"them. Personally, I would recommend a balanced force of two archers, two "
"fighters, and a shaman."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:228
msgid "Recruit or recall your troops"
msgstr "Recruit or recall your troops"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:242
msgid "Elvish Shaman"
msgstr "Elvish Shaman"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:243
msgid ""
"The Shaman is a fairly weak unit, but she has the ability to <i>heal</i> "
"friendly units around her. She also has a special attack which <i>slows</i> "
"enemies, halving the damage they do for one turn."
msgstr ""
"The Shaman is a fairly weak unit, but she has the ability to <i>heal</i> "
"friendly units around her. She also has a special attack which <i>slows</i> "
"enemies, halving the damage they do for one turn."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:248
msgid "Abilities and Weapon Specials"
msgstr "Abilities and Weapon Specials"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:250
msgid ""
"Certain unit types have special <i>abilities</i>. Unlike traits, which "
"usually provide small buffs or debuffs, abilities give units special "
"behaviors that normal units do not have. In this case, the Elvish Shaman has "
"the Heal ability, which allows her to heal allied adjacent units 4 hitpoints "
"at the start of each turn. Unit types with abilities, especially ones like "
"Heal, can be very useful, so be careful when sending them into battle.\n"
"\n"
"Weapon specials are special attack modifiers that make certain attacks more "
"powerful. Once again, in this case, the Shaman has the Slows special on her "
"entangle attack. When this attack is used on an enemy, it will halve the "
"damage they do for one turn. Other weapon specials include First Strike, "
"which allows that attack to always hit first no matter who attacks first, "
"and Magical, which gives that attack a constant 70% chance to hit.\n"
"\n"
"A full list of abilities and weapons specials, along with traits, may be "
"found in help."
msgstr ""
"Certain unit types have special <i>abilities</i>. Unlike traits, which "
"usually provide small buffs or debuffs, abilities give units special "
"behaviours that normal units do not have. In this case, the Elvish Shaman "
"has the Heal ability, which allows her to heal allied adjacent units 4 hit-"
"points at the start of each turn. Unit types with abilities, especially ones "
"like Heal, can be very useful, so be careful when sending them into battle.\n"
"\n"
"Weapon specials are special attack modifiers that make certain attacks more "
"powerful. Once again, in this case, the Shaman has the Slows special on her "
"entangle attack. When this attack is used on an enemy, it will halve the "
"damage they do for one turn. Other weapon specials include First Strike, "
"which allows that attack to always hit first no matter who attacks first, "
"and Magical, which gives that attack a constant 70% chance to hit.\n"
"\n"
"A full list of abilities and weapons specials, along with traits, may be "
"found in help."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:269
msgid "Elvish Archer"
msgstr "Elvish Archer"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:270
msgid ""
"Unlike the Elvish Fighter, which has strong melee attacks, the Elvish Archer "
"has strong ranged attacks. It’s useful to attack enemy units with strong "
"melee attacks with strong ranged attacks, and vice versa. This allows your "
"units to take less damage when your enemy counterattacks."
msgstr ""
"Unlike the Elvish Fighter, which has strong melee attacks, the Elvish Archer "
"has strong ranged attacks. It’s useful to attack enemy units with strong "
"melee attacks with strong ranged attacks, and vice versa. This allows your "
"units to take less damage when your enemy counter-attacks."

#. [message]: speaker=Galdrad
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:293
msgid ""
"You certainly have a fondness for shamans, I see. They will provide a lot of "
"healing, but not much offensive potential."
msgstr ""
"You certainly have a fondness for shamans, I see. They will provide a lot of "
"healing, but not much offensive potential."

#. [message]: speaker=Galdrad
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:304
msgid ""
"While none of your recruited units can move yet, you still can. You need "
"more income; there are some villages near the keep you can capture."
msgstr ""
"While none of your recruited units can move yet, you still can. You need "
"more income; there are some villages near the keep you can capture."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:307
msgid "Capture a village"
msgstr "Capture a village"

#. [message]: speaker=Galdrad
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:322
msgid ""
"Excellent! As Delfador mentioned earlier, each captured village will support "
"one unit and provide you with 1 extra gold per turn."
msgstr ""
"Excellent! As Delfador mentioned earlier, each captured village will support "
"one unit and provide you with 1 extra gold per turn."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:327
msgid "Income and Upkeep"
msgstr "Income and Upkeep"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:329
msgid ""
"Each turn, you will gain 2 gold plus one for each village you own. However, "
"<i>upkeep</i> is subtracted from that. You can support as many levels worth "
"of units as the number of villages you own; beyond that, you must pay 1 gold "
"per turn. Be careful, as owning too many units can cause you to have "
"negative income and lose gold each turn!"
msgstr ""
"Each turn, you will gain 2 gold plus one for each village you own. However, "
"<i>upkeep</i> is subtracted from that. You can support as many levels worth "
"of units as the number of villages you own; beyond that, you must pay 1 gold "
"per turn. Be careful, as owning too many units can cause you to have "
"negative income and lose gold each turn!"

#. [message]: speaker=Galdrad
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:345
msgid ""
"Now, young man, it is time to discuss strategy. Your units are ready to "
"attack, and the orcish leader has begun gathering his own troops."
msgstr ""
"Now, young man, it is time to discuss strategy. Your units are ready to "
"attack, and the orcish leader has begun gathering his own troops."

#. [message]: speaker=Galdrad
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:350
msgid ""
"Now, young lady, it is time to discuss strategy. Your units are ready to "
"attack, and the orcish leader has begun gathering his own troops."
msgstr ""
"Now, young lady, it is time to discuss strategy. Your units are ready to "
"attack, and the orcish leader has begun gathering his own troops."

#. [message]: speaker=student
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:356
msgid ""
"Galdrad, if I go by the ford, I could sneak up near his keep and dispatch "
"him quickly."
msgstr ""
"Galdrad, if I go by the ford, I could sneak up near his keep and dispatch "
"him quickly."

#. [message]: speaker=Galdrad
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:361
msgid ""
"You could. However, elves (and orcs) have bad <i>defense</i> in water. "
"You’ll be more vulnerable as you try to wade slowly across the ford; the "
"enemy will have an 80% chance to hit you. Since elves have good defense in "
"the forest, I would advise you keep to the trees and attack the orcs from "
"there; you’ll only have a 40% chance of being hit in return."
msgstr ""
"You could. However, elves (and orcs) have bad <i>defence</i> in water. "
"You’ll be more vulnerable as you try to wade slowly across the ford; the "
"enemy will have an 80% chance to hit you. Since elves have good defence in "
"the forest, I would advise you keep to the trees and attack the orcs from "
"there; you’ll only have a 40% chance of being hit in return."

#. [message]: speaker=Galdrad
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:366
msgid ""
"However, keep an eye on that ford. The orcs may try to sneak around behind "
"our forces. It might do to send a few units to defend the banks, and the "
"village there."
msgstr ""
"However, keep an eye on that ford. The orcs may try to sneak around behind "
"our forces. It might do to send a few units to defend the banks, and the "
"village there."

#. [message]: speaker=student
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:371
msgid ""
"Alright. The bridge it is, then, but I’ll be careful about the crossing."
msgstr ""
"All right. The bridge it is, then, but I’ll be careful about the crossing."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:374
msgid ""
"That Orcish Grunt is still blocking our path. He has no ranged attacks, so "
"your archers should be able to engage him with little risk. Unfortunately, "
"your units cannot reach him this turn, but you should not let them languish! "
"Move them into position so they can attack next turn. There are also other "
"villages on this side of the river. You should secure them for income and "
"healing"
msgstr ""
"That Orcish Grunt is still blocking our path. He has no ranged attacks, so "
"your archers should be able to engage him with little risk. Unfortunately, "
"your units cannot reach him this turn, but you should not let them languish! "
"Move them into position so they can attack next turn. There are also other "
"villages on this side of the river. You should secure them for income and "
"healing."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:378
msgid "Long-distance Movement"
msgstr "Long-distance Movement"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:380
msgid ""
"You can order a unit to move for multiple turns by selecting the unit and "
"clicking on the destination. A number will indicate how many turns it will "
"take to get there."
msgstr ""
"You can order a unit to move for multiple turns by selecting the unit and "
"clicking on the destination. A number will indicate how many turns it will "
"take to get there."

#. [message]: speaker=student
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:385
msgid ""
"I think I’ll stick around the keep for now, in order to recruit more units."
msgstr ""
"I think I’ll stick around the keep for now, in order to recruit more units."

#. [message]: speaker=Galdrad
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:391
msgid ""
"You’ve learned well, Konrad. It is indeed a good idea to keep your leader "
"safe and protected and in range of your keep early in the game. The tide of "
"battle can turn quickly, and you don’t want to find yourself cut off from "
"recruiting reinforcements."
msgstr ""
"You’ve learned well, Konrad. It is indeed a good idea to keep your leader "
"safe and protected and in range of your keep early in the game. The tide of "
"battle can turn quickly, and you don’t want to find yourself cut off from "
"recruiting reinforcements."

#. [message]: speaker=Galdrad
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:396
msgid ""
"You’ve learned well, Li’sar. It is indeed a good idea to keep your leader "
"safe and protected and in range of your keep early in the game. The tide of "
"battle can turn quickly, and you don’t want to find yourself cut off from "
"recruiting reinforcements."
msgstr ""
"You’ve learned well, Li’sar. It is indeed a good idea to keep your leader "
"safe and protected and in range of your keep early in the game. The tide of "
"battle can turn quickly, and you don’t want to find yourself cut off from "
"recruiting reinforcements."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:406
msgid "Tracking Enemy Movement"
msgstr "Tracking Enemy Movement"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:408
msgid ""
"You can see where an enemy can reach by moving the mouse over them. You can "
"see all possible enemy moves at once with the <b>Show Enemy Moves</b> "
"command from the <b>Actions</b> menu."
msgstr ""
"You can see where an enemy can reach by moving the mouse over them. You can "
"see all possible enemy moves at once with the <b>Show Enemy Moves</b> "
"command from the <b>Actions</b> menu."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:411
msgid "We must occupy that island before the Wolf Riders reach it!"
msgstr "We must occupy that island before the Wolf Riders reach it!"

#. [message]: speaker=student
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:416
msgid "Can’t we just move around the orcs?"
msgstr "Can’t we just move around the orcs?"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:429
msgid ""
"No. Once you move close to an enemy unit, you are in its <i>Zone of Control</"
"i> and cannot move further that turn. To move your troops onto that island "
"without wading slowly through the water, you’ll have to kill the Grunt."
msgstr ""
"No. Once you move close to an enemy unit, you are in its <i>Zone of Control</"
"i> and cannot move further that turn. To move your troops on to that island "
"without wading slowly through the water, you’ll have to kill the Grunt."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:433
msgid "Zone of Control"
msgstr "Zone of Control"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:435
msgid ""
"The hexes immediately around a unit constitute its <i>Zone of Control</i>. "
"When an enemy unit enters those hexes, they cannot move any further that "
"turn. An exception are units with the <i>skirmish</i> ability, who are "
"unaffected by zones of control. This can be used to create a blockade to "
"prevent stronger enemies from reaching key locations, such as villages, even "
"if you have limited manpower."
msgstr ""
"The hexes immediately around a unit constitute its <i>Zone of Control</i>. "
"When an enemy unit enters those hexes, they cannot move any further that "
"turn. An exception are units with the <i>skirmish</i> ability, who are "
"unaffected by zones of control. This can be used to create a blockade to "
"prevent stronger enemies from reaching key locations, such as villages, even "
"if you have limited manpower."

#. [message]: speaker=student
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:450
msgid ""
"I hope my units survive the counter-attack if I can’t take this grunt out "
"this turn. I’d better grab more villages if I can and move everyone closer "
"for next turn."
msgstr ""
"I hope my units survive the counter-attack if I can’t take this grunt out "
"this turn. I’d better grab more villages if I can and move everyone closer "
"for next turn."

#. [message]: speaker=Galdrad
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:455
msgid ""
"If one of your Shamans stands just behind your wounded units, she will heal "
"them each 4 hitpoints at the beginning of the next turn."
msgstr ""
"If one of your Shamans stands just behind your wounded units, she will heal "
"them each 4 hit-points at the beginning of the next turn."

#. [message]: speaker=second_unit
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:468
msgid ""
"One fewer orc to deal with, and our way across the bridge is clear! I also "
"gained experience from striking the killing blow!"
msgstr ""
"One fewer orc to deal with, and our way across the bridge is clear! I also "
"gained experience from striking the killing blow!"

#. [message]: speaker=Galdrad
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:489
msgid ""
"Be careful! If you stand on the bridge you are exposed to attack from "
"multiple directions! Even though the orcs have low defense in water, they "
"will overwhelm you with their numbers."
msgstr ""
"Be careful! If you stand on the bridge you are exposed to attack from "
"multiple directions! Even though the orcs have low defence in water, they "
"will overwhelm you with their numbers."

#. [message]: speaker=Galdrad
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:505
msgid ""
"Well done! The island village is ours. You can use the trees to set up a "
"blockade against the orcs; they can only come across the bridge one by one "
"without wading through the water, and you will be securely on a terrain with "
"good defense."
msgstr ""
"Well done! The island village is ours. You can use the trees to set up a "
"blockade against the orcs; they can only come across the bridge one by one "
"without wading through the water, and you will be securely on a terrain with "
"good defence."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:508
msgid ""
"Don’t forget about that last village near the channel. They orcs will "
"capture if it they try to sneak around via the ford! It will be hard to "
"dislodge them of they do."
msgstr ""
"Don’t forget about that last village near the channel. They orcs will "
"capture if it they try to sneak around via the ford! It will be hard to "
"dislodge them of they do."

#. [message]: speaker=Galdrad
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:522
msgid ""
"It’s very dangerous to stand in water when there are enemies about! Your "
"unit will have an 80% chance of being hit. Get back, and wait for them to "
"attack you!"
msgstr ""
"It’s very dangerous to stand in water when there are enemies about! Your "
"unit will have an 80% chance of being hit! Cancel, and wait It’s very "
"dangerous to stand in water when there are enemies about! Your unit will "
"have an 80% chance of being hit. Get back, and wait for them to attack you!"
"for them to attack you!"

#. [message]: speaker=Galdrad
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:545
msgid ""
"You’re venturing away from your keep. You might need recruit more units, and "
"I doubt the orc leader will let you use his! Careful!"
msgstr ""
"You’re venturing away from your keep. You might need recruit more units, and "
"I doubt the orc leader will let you use his! Careful!"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:562
msgid ""
"We need to occupy that village, otherwise they will take it next turn! Move "
"a unit into the village to stop the orcs capturing it. Whichever unit you "
"choose will benefit from the village’s healing, too."
msgstr ""
"We need to occupy that village, otherwise they will take it next turn! Move "
"a unit into the village to stop the orcs capturing it. Whichever unit you "
"choose will benefit from the village’s healing, too."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:568
msgid ""
"Careful! It is now nighttime. Orcs are <i>chaotic</i>, which means their "
"attacks are now 25% stronger. By day, their attacks are 25% weaker, which is "
"a noticeable difference. You are <i>lawful</i>: stronger by day and weaker "
"at night. Your elvish warriors are <i>neutral</i>: unaffected by the time of "
"day."
msgstr ""
"Careful! It is now night-time. Orcs are <i>chaotic</i>, which means their "
"attacks are now 25% stronger. By day, their attacks are 25% weaker, which is "
"a noticeable difference. You are <i>lawful</i>: stronger by day and weaker "
"at night. Your elvish warriors are <i>neutral</i>: unaffected by the time of "
"day."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:572
msgid "Time of Day"
msgstr "Time of Day"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:574
msgid ""
"During a scenario, the time of day will shift as turns pass. There are four "
"<i>alignments</i> a unit may be: Lawful, Neutral, Chaotic, or Liminal. Each "
"alignment gets a different bonus or handicap depending on the time of day. "
"You can mouse over the landscape image below the minimap on the right to see "
"the current time of day and who has the advantage."
msgstr ""
"During a scenario, the time of day will shift as turns pass. There are four "
"<i>alignments</i> a unit may be: Lawful, Neutral, Chaotic, or Liminal. Each "
"alignment gets a different bonus or handicap depending on the time of day. "
"You can mouse over the landscape image below the mini-map on the right to "
"see the current time of day and who has the advantage."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:585
msgid ""
"Remember to retreat your wounded units to villages. Healers can only heal 4 "
"hitpoints at a time, while villages can heal 8 (the maximum healing for any "
"unit)."
msgstr ""
"Remember to retreat your wounded units to villages. Healers can only heal 4 "
"hit-points at a time, while villages can heal 8 (the maximum healing for any "
"unit)."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:595
msgid ""
"Beware of those orcs crossing the river! If they get into the forest they’ll "
"be hard to dislodge!"
msgstr ""
"Beware of those orcs crossing the river! If they get into the forest they’ll "
"be hard to dislodge!"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:603
msgid "Tracking Unused Units"
msgstr "Tracking Unused Units"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:605
msgid ""
"You can ensure you use all your troops by pressing <b>n</b> to step from one "
"unit to the next. If you press <b>space</b>, you can mark the currently "
"selected unit as having finished its turn, which stops you moving it by "
"accident later on. When <b>n</b> no longer selects a new unit, it’s safe to "
"end your turn."
msgstr ""
"You can ensure you use all your troops by pressing <b>n</b> to step from one "
"unit to the next. If you press <b>space</b>, you can mark the currently "
"selected unit as having finished its turn, which stops you moving it by "
"accident later on. When <b>n</b> no longer selects a new unit, it’s safe to "
"end your turn."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:614
msgid "Victory Conditions"
msgstr "Victory Conditions"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:616
msgid ""
"In this scenario, you only need to defeat the orc leader to win. Victory "
"conditions for a scenario are given under <b>Scenario Objectives</b> in  "
"<b>Menu</b>)."
msgstr ""
"In this scenario, you only need to defeat the orc leader to win. Victory "
"conditions for a scenario are given under <b>Scenario Objectives</b> in  "
"<b>Menu</b>)."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:625
msgid "Recruit the Right Units"
msgstr "Recruit the Right Units"

# TODO: maybe add a serial comma to this and the original
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:627
msgid ""
"Remember to recruit troops useful for the situation. Archers are "
"particularly effective against Grunts, Wolf Riders and the orcish leader."
msgstr ""
"Remember to recruit troops useful for the situation. Archers are "
"particularly effective against Grunts, Wolf Riders and the orcish leader."

#. [message]: speaker=student
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:654
msgid "I have enough gold to recruit more units!"
msgstr "I have enough gold to recruit more units!"

#. [message]: speaker=Galdrad
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:708
msgid ""
"That unit is about one kill (8 experience points) away from gaining a level! "
"Do not let it die!"
msgstr ""
"That unit is about one kill (8 experience points) away from gaining a level! "
"Do not let it die!"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:730
msgid ""
"Their leader has moved into that village! He’s not as stupid as I thought. "
"The village heals him each turn and provides good defense."
msgstr ""
"Their leader has moved into that village! He’s not as stupid as I thought. "
"The village heals him each turn and provides good defence."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:741
msgid ""
"That unit has captured our village! You’d better get him out; it heals him "
"each turn and provides good defense."
msgstr ""
"That unit has captured our village! You’d better get him out; it heals him "
"each turn and provides good defence."

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:753
msgid ""
"Using me to attack is risky! I can slow the opponent with my ranged attack, "
"but I hope you have a plan if I miss!"
msgstr ""
"Using me to attack is risky! I can slow the opponent with my ranged attack, "
"but I hope you have a plan if I miss!"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:769
msgid ""
"You are close to killing their leader! The unit who finishes him will gain "
"16 experience points because he is second level. Choose your attacking unit "
"carefully!"
msgstr ""
"You are close to killing their leader! The unit who finishes him will gain "
"16 experience points because he is second level. Choose your attacking unit "
"carefully!"

#. [message]: speaker=Galdrad
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:794
msgid ""
"We will miss $unit.name| because he had $unit.experience experience points. "
"He would have advanced a level soon."
msgstr ""
"We will miss $unit.name| because he had $unit.experience experience points. "
"He would have advanced a level soon."

#. [message]: speaker=Galdrad
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:800
msgid ""
"We will miss $unit.name| because she had $unit.experience experience points. "
"She would have advanced a level soon."
msgstr ""
"We will miss $unit.name| because she had $unit.experience experience points. "
"She would have advanced a level soon."

#. [message]: speaker=Galdrad
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:829
msgid ""
"We will miss $unit.name|, but at least he was not one of our experienced "
"troops!"
msgstr ""
"We will miss $unit.name|, but at least he was not one of our experienced "
"troops!"

#. [message]: speaker=Galdrad
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:835
msgid ""
"We will miss $unit.name|, but at least she was not one of our experienced "
"troops!"
msgstr ""
"We will miss $unit.name|, but at least she was not one of our experienced "
"troops!"

#. [message]: speaker=Galdrad
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:855
msgid ""
"Higher level units are powerful, but not invulnerable. Goodbye, $unit.name|."
msgstr ""
"Higher level units are powerful, but not invulnerable. Goodbye, $unit.name|."

#. [message]: speaker=Galdrad
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:869
msgid ""
"Losing a healer hurts all the troops! Keep them out of the enemy’s reach!"
msgstr ""
"Losing a healer hurts all the troops! Keep them out of the enemy’s reach!"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:881
msgid ""
"Beware of the orc leader: he can do 36 hitpoints of damage at night! Attack "
"with many units at once during the day."
msgstr ""
"Beware of the orc leader: he can do 36 hit-points of damage at night! Attack "
"with many units at once during the day."

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:894
msgid ""
"Advancing a level has fully healed me! I am able to heal units 8 hitpoints "
"per turn, instead of just 4, and may also cure them of poison if they cannot "
"reach a village! I also have gained a new <i>magical</i> attack, meaning it "
"always has a 70% chance to hit, but it is not as powerful as the similar "
"attack wielded by the Elvish Sorceress."
msgstr ""
"Advancing a level has fully healed me! I am able to heal units 8 hit-points "
"per turn, instead of just 4, and may also cure them of poison if they cannot "
"reach a village! I also have gained a new <i>magical</i> attack, meaning it "
"always has a 70% chance to hit, but it is not as powerful as the similar "
"attack wielded by the Elvish Sorceress."

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:907
msgid ""
"Advancing a level has fully healed me! I cannot heal adjacent units anymore, "
"but to compensate, I have a new, powerful faerie fire attack that deals 7 "
"damage each for 4 strikes. It also has the <i>magical</i> weapon special, "
"meaning it always has a 70% chance to hit."
msgstr ""
"Advancing a level has fully healed me! I cannot heal adjacent units any "
"more, but to compensate, I have a new, powerful faerie fire attack that "
"deals 7 damage each for 4 strikes. It also has the <i>magical</i> weapon "
"special, meaning it always has a 70% chance to hit."

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:921
msgid ""
"Advancing a level has fully healed me! I always have a 60% chance of hitting "
"with my <i>Marksman</i> ability, and I deal 9 damage each for 4 attacks. Use "
"me to dislodge hard-to-hit units."
msgstr ""
"Advancing a level has fully healed me! I always have a 60% chance of hitting "
"with my <i>Marksman</i> ability, and I deal 9 damage each for 4 attacks. Use "
"me to dislodge hard-to-hit units."

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:934
msgid ""
"Advancing a level has fully healed me! I am good with both bow and sword, "
"and I have a special ability: <i>Ambush</i>. I can hide in forests where "
"enemies can only see me if they are right next to me."
msgstr ""
"Advancing a level has fully healed me! I am good with both bow and sword, "
"and I have a special ability: <i>Ambush</i>. I can hide in forests where "
"enemies can only see me if they are right next to me."

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:948
msgid ""
"Advancing a level has fully healed me! I am good with both bow and sword, "
"and I have a special ability: <i>Leadership</i>. I do less damage myself "
"than the Elvish Hero, but my ability allows my allies to fight better. First "
"level units around me do 25% more damage, so position me carefully!"
msgstr ""
"Advancing a level has fully healed me! I am good with both bow and sword, "
"and I have a special ability: <i>Leadership</i>. I do less damage myself "
"than the Elvish Hero, but my ability allows my allies to fight better. First "
"level units around me do 25% more damage, so position me carefully!"

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:961
msgid ""
"Advancing a level has fully healed me! I am particularly good with the "
"sword, dealing 8 damage in 4 attacks. While I don’t have the Leadership "
"abilities of the Elvish Captain, my superior fighting skills allow my "
"attacks to do more damage!"
msgstr ""
"Advancing a level has fully healed me! I am particularly good with the "
"sword, dealing 8 damage in 4 attacks. While I don’t have the Leadership "
"abilities of the Elvish Captain, my superior fighting skills allow my "
"attacks to do more damage!"

#. [message]: speaker=Galdrad
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:970
msgid "You took too long! Now we’ll never be rid of these orcs!"
msgstr "You took too long! Now we’ll never be rid of these orcs!"

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:986
msgid "That... was foolish. Next time I should be more careful."
msgstr "That... was foolish. Next time I should be more careful."

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:1009
msgid "Agh! Now who will teach you how to defeat these orcs!"
msgstr "Agh! Now who will teach you how to defeat these orcs!"

#. [message]: speaker=Galdrad
#: data/campaigns/tutorial/scenarios/02_Tutorial_part_2.cfg:1035
msgid ""
"You have beaten the orcs! You may want to try some novice-level campaigns "
"next, such as: <i>The South Guard</i>, <i>An Orcish Incursion</i>, <i>A Tale "
"of Two Brothers</i>, or <i>Heir to the Throne</i>. <i>The South Guard</i> "
"was specifically designed as a beginner’s campaign. Konrad, Li’sar and "
"Delfador are characters from <i>Heir to the Throne</i>. You can also refer "
"to the in-game help browser if you ever need to refresh your memory on "
"gameplay mechanics."
msgstr ""
"You have beaten the orcs! You may want to try some novice-level campaigns "
